1. Setup instructions

Fill these environment variables:
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
GEMINI_API_KEY
GEMINI_MODEL
SUPADATA_API_KEY
SUPADATA_BASE_URL
SERPAPI_API_KEY
SERPAPI_BASE_URL
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
CLOUDFLARE_AI_IMAGE_MODEL
DODO_PAYMENTS_API_KEY
DODO_PAYMENTS_WEBHOOK_KEY
DODO_PAYMENTS_ENVIRONMENT
DODO_PAYMENTS_RETURN_URL
DODO_PAYMENTS_PORTAL_RETURN_URL
DODO_PAYMENTS_PLUS_PRODUCT_ID
DODO_PAYMENTS_PRO_PRODUCT_ID

Supabase setup for a fresh project:
Create a Supabase project.
Open SQL Editor.
Paste the full contents of supabase/schema.sql.
Run it.

If you already created the database from the older Version 1 schema, run supabase/v2_upgrade.sql after that.

In Project Settings → API, copy:
Project URL
Publishable key
Service role key

In Authentication → Providers → Email, keep email/password enabled.
Disable Confirm Email if you want signup to land in the dashboard immediately.

How plans work in this build:
Free users get:
tier = 'free'
monthly_generation_limit = 5
image limit = 1 per month
billing_status = 'inactive'

Plus users get:
tier = 'plus'
monthly_generation_limit = null
image limit = 5 per month
billing_status = 'active'

Pro users get:
tier = 'pro'
monthly_generation_limit = null
image limit = unlimited
billing_status = 'active'

Dodo Payments setup:
Create two subscription products in Dodo Payments: one for Plus and one for Pro.
Copy the product IDs into DODO_PAYMENTS_PLUS_PRODUCT_ID and DODO_PAYMENTS_PRO_PRODUCT_ID.
Create an API key in Developer → API Keys and copy it into DODO_PAYMENTS_API_KEY.
Create a webhook in Settings → Webhooks.
Set the endpoint to:
https://your-domain.com/api/dodo/webhook
Subscribe to at least these events:
payment.succeeded
subscription.active
subscription.updated
subscription.renewed
subscription.plan_changed
subscription.on_hold
subscription.failed
subscription.cancelled
subscription.expired
Copy the webhook secret into DODO_PAYMENTS_WEBHOOK_KEY.
Set DODO_PAYMENTS_ENVIRONMENT to test_mode while testing and live_mode in production.
Set DODO_PAYMENTS_RETURN_URL to your deployed success page, usually https://your-domain.com/checkout/success.
Set DODO_PAYMENTS_PORTAL_RETURN_URL to your profile page, usually https://your-domain.com/profile.

What the Dodo integration does in this build:
Pricing buttons create a real checkout session on your server.
Checkout metadata stores the selected plan and your Supabase user id.
After payment, the Dodo webhook updates public.profiles automatically.
Paid users can open the Dodo customer portal from Profile once billing_customer_id exists.

Manual upgrade SQL for testing paid plans:
update public.profiles
set
  tier = 'plus',
  monthly_generation_limit = null,
  billing_status = 'active'
where email = 'user@example.com';

Or for Pro:
update public.profiles
set
  tier = 'pro',
  monthly_generation_limit = null,
  billing_status = 'active'
where email = 'user@example.com';

Gemini text setup:
Create the API key in Google AI Studio and place it in GEMINI_API_KEY.
Recommended text model default: gemini-2.5-flash

YouTube transcript provider setup:
Add SUPADATA_API_KEY for the primary transcript provider.
Optional: set SUPADATA_BASE_URL if you need a custom base URL.
Add SERPAPI_API_KEY for the fallback transcript provider.
Optional: set SERPAPI_BASE_URL if you need a custom SerpApi endpoint.
Transcript order in this build: Supadata -> SerpApi -> youtube-transcript.

Cloudflare image setup:
In Cloudflare, create an API token for Workers AI and copy your Account ID.
Recommended image model default: @cf/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0

2. Run instructions

Install dependencies:
npm install

Create .env.local from .env.example and paste your real values.
Do not commit .env.local.

Start local dev:
npm run dev

Open:
http://localhost:3000

Vercel deploy:
Push the project to GitHub
Import the repo into Vercel
Add the same environment variables in Vercel Project Settings
Deploy

Production notes:
This app already includes:
plan-aware UI locks
server-enforced monthly text usage caps
server-enforced monthly image usage caps
DB tier tracking
private history saving
multi-platform generation
YouTube transcript fallback chain (Supadata -> SerpApi -> youtube-transcript)
Gemini text generation
Cloudflare image generation
Dodo Payments checkout
Dodo Payments webhook-driven plan activation
Dodo Payments customer portal


Security / bot protection
- Add Cloudflare Turnstile keys in Vercel:
  NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY
  TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY
- Run supabase/v2_upgrade.sql again to create auth_rate_limits for login throttling.
- In Supabase dashboard also turn on Bot and Abuse Protection with Cloudflare Turnstile and tighten Authentication > Rate Limits.
